 theoretical approach, engaging with local and contextual forms of peacebuilding agency and including local authorsContinues the project begun in Oliver Richmond's 2009 book Liberal Peace Transitions"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aIntervention (International law) 0aIntervention (International law). 0aNation-building. 0aPeace-building. 4aPolitics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh1 aBelloni, Roberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBijlert, Martine van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoege, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBøås, Morten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDemetriou, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGinty, Roger Mac, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHadjipavlou, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHughes, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKappler, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopes, Paula Duarte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNetra, Eng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPogodda, Sandra, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPogodda, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamovic, Jasmin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichmond, Oliver P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTom, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVisoka, Gëzim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc